This paper deals with visual odometry, which is a subfield of robotics and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also proposes a deep learning approach to improve the accuracy of visual odometry, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of self-supervised learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data-driven learning to regress pose corrections, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with navigation accuracy, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
